dc_title_s: The Moguls empire divided into its principal governments
dc_description_s: Extent: 1 map | Abstract: Map of part of India, and a small part of Sri Lanka, showing the Mughal empire and its successor states. | Notes: Relief shown pictorially.|From the Gentleman's magazine, London, March, 1767.|Detached from: The gentleman's magazine, and historical chronicle. Volume XXXVII : for the year M.DCC.LXVII. London : Printed... for D. Henry, 1766. Map was originally published in the March 1767 issue, following page 98. | Scale approximately 1:11,600,000
